description: Number of trees T of order n such that W(T) = W(L(L(T)) where W(G) and L(G) are the Wiener index and line graph of a graph G.
references: A. A. Dobrynin (dobr(AT)math.nsc.ru), Distance of iterated line graphs, Graph Theory Notes of NY, 37 (1999), 8-9.
A. A. Dobrynin and L. S. Mel'nikov, Some results on the Wiener index of iterated line graphs, Electronic Notes in Discrete Mathematics 22 (2005), 469-475
links: Index entries for sequences related to trees
prog: (Sage) # needs the package nautydef a(n):    c = 0    for el in graphs.nauty_geng(str(n) + ' -c ' + str(n-1)+':' + str(n-1)):        g = (el.line_graph()).line_graph()        if el.wiener_index() == g.wiener_index():            c+=1    return c# _Jernej Azarija_, Aug 13 2012
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
extensions: More terms (from Dobrynin/Mel'nikov reference), _Jernej Azarija_, Aug 13 2012.
